Formal Talks

When giving a formal talk, we can use a range of expressions to show progession from the beginning of the talk to the ending.


Beginning
Before we begin, I'd like to thank the organizers. 

I'd like to start with some background, I'd like to start by asking you all a question.

The first part of my talk is about the history of this building.


Middle
I'd like to go on to talk about the current situation.

Next, I'd like to talk about our plans for the future.

Ending
I'd like to conclude by summarizing the main points of today's talk.

To conclude, I'd like to give you a quick summary of main points.

